Access Messaging and Voice Conversation Data

Conversation Transcript Export

Salesforce admins can export conversation transcripts for Voice, Messaging, enhanced Facebook Messenger, and enhanced WhatsApp in any production org.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS

Available in: Lightning Experience
Messaging...and Facebook Messenger. View required editions.
Service Cloud Voice in Enterprise and Unlimited Editions.

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To export conversation transcripts:
Weekly Data Export
System Administrator

NOTE If your Salesforce subscriptions expire or contact Salesforce Customer Support to cancel it, you can still export conversation transcript data while your org is locked if you ask Salesforce Customer Support to temporarily unlock your org.

TIP Conversation transcripts don’t count towards your Salesforce org’s storage limits and usage calculations.

Add our file storage URL (https://*.amazonaws.com) as a Trusted URL.
In the Content Security Policy Settings, select Lightning Experience pages.
Click Export Now to download your data.
When the download is complete, you see one or more download buttons. Click Download Data for each row of data that you want to download.

Any data generated after clicking Export Now is not reflected in the export. To capture additional data, wait 7 days and re-export your data. Doing so replaces the previous exported data. The related export data and its audit data is available until 30 days from the date of last successful export.
title: Exporting Conversation Transcripts in Service Cloud
